        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 3 at 6:45PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 645 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles northwest of Robbinsville, or 7 miles northwest of Town Of
Santeetlah, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Wesser, Stecoah, Smoky Mountains-Fontana Area, Nantahala, Lake
Santeetlah, Cheoah, Deals Gap, Fontana Lake, Almond, and
Robbinsville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
